message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. The paper deals with machine reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also utilizes neural networks for answer extraction and verification, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper investigates different architectures for the answer verifier, which is related to neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, as it aims to extract answers from input snippets, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
